2004-07-24 17:08:38 GMT	J. David Ibanez <jdavid@itaapy.com>	patch-51

    Summary:
      Add __setitem__ to file resources, to allow direct write.
    Revision:
      itools--main--0.4--patch-51

    Now it is possible to directly modify file resources at specific positions,
    as now __setitem__ is implemented (for memory and file resources so far).
    Example of use:
    
      resource[base:base+size] = slice
    
    Where the slice's length is size.

    modified files:
     resources/base.py resources/file.py resources/memory.py


