2004-06-11 17:54:25 GMT	J. David Ibanez <jdavid@itaapy.com>	patch-26

    Summary:
      add the method _get_virtual_handler to folder handlers
    Revision:
      itools--main--0.4--patch-26

    Add the method "_get_virtual_handler(segment)" to folder handlers.
    It is called by "get_handler" when the requested resource does not
    exist, so we have a chance to do something "magic" and return a
    "virtual" handler for a resource that lives somewhere else.
    
    Before it was the "_get_handler(segment)" who had to deal with these
    situations. Now it only must return a handler for resources that
    exists; its new prototype is "_get_handler(segment, resource).
    
    Beware, this API change is likely to break existing code.

    modified files:
     handlers/Folder.py


