2004-06-06 18:56:15 GMT	J. David Ibanez <jdavid@itaapy.com>	patch-19

    Summary:
      consider the XML doctype to choose the right handler class
    Revision:
      itools--main--0.4--patch-19

    Modify the XML registry to keep record of document types (besides
    namespaces). Add the factory function "xml.XML.get_handler", it
    uses the registry to return a handler of the right handler class.
    
    As a result "handlers.get_handler" now takes into account the doctype
    information of XML documents to return the right handler.

    modified files:
     handlers/__init__.py xml/RDF.py xml/STL.py xml/Schema.py
     xml/XHTML.py xml/XML.py xml/__init__.py xml/test_xsd.py


